================================================================================
Third-party components and data — license matrix
================================================================================

tracecal is a dataset-AUDITING HARNESS for LeRobot robot-learning datasets. It
does NOT bundle or redistribute any robot model, manufacturer URDF, policy
weights, or dataset. Each component below is fetched/installed by the end user
under that project's own license, and is invoked only when its optional extra is
installed.

Dataset format / loading (opt-in `hub` extra):

  LeRobot / LeRobotDataset v3   Apache-2.0   — huggingface/lerobot dataset format.
                                               Episodes (parquet) are loaded with
                                               pyarrow; the `lerobot` library and
                                               torch are NOT imported at runtime.
  huggingface_hub               Apache-2.0   — Hub download of public datasets.
  pyarrow                       Apache-2.0   — parquet reader.

Robot models / URDF (opt-in `physics` extra; URDFs are NOT redistributed here):

  robot_descriptions.py         Apache-2.0   — fetches manufacturer URDFs on demand
                                               into the user's cache. tracecal never
                                               vendors a manufacturer URDF.
  yourdfpy                      MIT          — URDF parser (joint-limit extraction).

  Manufacturer URDFs fetched THROUGH robot_descriptions retain their own licenses,
  e.g. Franka Emika `franka_description` (Apache-2.0), Universal Robots
  `ur_description` (BSD-3-Clause), KUKA iiwa / UFACTORY xArm descriptions. tracecal
  only reads joint limits from them at the user's request; it redistributes none.

Test fixtures:

  tests/fixtures/urdf/*.urdf     — minimal, hand-authored synthetic 2-3 link arms
                                   written FOR this project (Apache-2.0). They are
                                   NOT derived from any manufacturer model and exist
                                   only to exercise the parser/gate in CI offline.

Conformal cross-check (opt-in `crosscheck` extra; test-only, never imported at runtime):

  crepes                         BSD-3-Clause — independent reference for the
                                                split-conformal p-values.
  scikit-learn                   BSD-3-Clause — IsotonicRegression cross-check of the
                                                in-house PAVA.

Core:

  numpy                          BSD-3-Clause
  scipy                          BSD-3-Clause
  pydantic                       MIT

Trademarks and product names (Franka Emika, Universal Robots, KUKA, UFACTORY,
ALOHA, SO-100/SO-101, Koch, LeKiwi) are the property of their respective owners
and are used here only to identify components a user may choose to install or
datasets a user may choose to audit.
